The paper deals with the problem of learning mixtures of generalized linear models (GLM) which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper proposes a tensor decomposition method for this problem, which is a popular technique in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of local optima, which is a common problem in optimization and can be addressed using techniques from the field of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category. The paper also involves the use of score function tensors, which is a concept from information theory (IT). Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely category. The paper also involves statistical analysis and the use of latent dimensions, which are concepts from statistics (ST) and signal processing (SI), respectively. Therefore, cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) are also likely categories.
